description: North Korea: Murder in the Family Sociopolitical Documentary hosted by Jane McMullan, published by BBC broadcasted as part of BBC This World series in 2017 - English narration http://docuwiki.net/images/9/9f/North-Korea-Murder-in-the-Family-Cover.jpg Information ------------------------------ North Korea: Murder in the Family On 13 February 2017, the North Korean dictator's half-brother Kim Jong-nam walked into Kuala Lumpur airport to catch a flight to Macau. Two hours later he was dead. He had been assassinated using one of the most deadly chemical weapons on earth - VX. Within days, two women from Vietnam and Indonesia were arrested for his murder, but the CCTV appeared to show several North Korean secret agents orchestrating the events in the airport that day.
